The '''Utah Wing''' of the '''Civil Air Patrol''' (CAP) is the highest echelon of [[Civil Air Patrol]] in the state of [[Utah]]. Utah Wing [[headquarters]] are located in [[Salt Lake City, Utah]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://cap.utah.gov/contact_utah_wing.html |title=Contact Utah Wing Headquarters |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date= |website=Utah Wing Civil Air Patrol Official Website |publisher= |access-date=3 December 2015}}</ref> The Utah Wing consists of over 500 cadet and adult members at over 13 locations across the state of Utah.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.capmembers.com/media/cms/UtahWing_HR_00A5006BCC208.pdf |title=2014 Statistics |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date= |website=Capmembers.com |publisher= |access-date=3 December 2015}}</ref>
==Mission== The Utah Wing performs the three primary missions of the Civil Air Patrol: providing [[emergency services]]; offering cadet programs for youth; and providing [[aerospace]] education for both Civil Air Patrol members and the general public.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gocivilairpatrol.com/ |title=Civil Air Patrol |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date= |website=Civil Air Patrol Official Website |publisher= |access-date=3 December 2015}}</ref>
===Emergency services=== The Civil Air Patrol performs emergency services, which includes performing [[search and rescue]] and [[disaster relief]] missions; as well as assisting in [[humanitarian aid]] assignments. CAP also provides [[United States Air Force|Air Force]] support through conducting light transport, communications support, and low-altitude route surveys. The Civil Air Patrol offers support to counter-drug missions.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gocivilairpatrol.com/about/civil_air_patrols_three_primary_missions/emergency-services/ |title=Emergency Services |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date= |website=Civil Air Patrol Official Website |publisher= |access-date=3 December 2015}}</ref>
===Cadet programs=== The Civil Air Patrol offers a cadet program for youth aged 12 to 21, which includes aerospace education, leadership training, physical fitness and moral leadership.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gocivilairpatrol.com/about/civil_air_patrols_three_primary_missions/cadet-programs/ |title=Cadet Programs |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date= |website=Civil Air Patrol Official Website |publisher= |access-date=3 December 2015}}</ref>
===Aerospace education=== The Civil Air Patrol offers aerospace education for CAP members and the general public, including providing training to the members of CAP, and offering workshops for youth throughout the nation through schools and public aviation events.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gocivilairpatrol.com/about/civil_air_patrols_three_primary_missions/ |title=Aerospace Education |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date= |website=Civil Air Patrol Official Website |publisher= |access-date=3 December 2015}}</ref>
